# **Observability Design**

This document establishes foundational observability infrastructure by deploying core monitoring components and basic telemetry collection without requiring custom instrumentation.

- Azure Monitor Container Insights for all container telemetry  
- Azure Monitor integration for centralized log and metrics aggregation  
- Policy-enforced diagnostic settings for all Azure resources

## **1\. Collection Methods and Service Coverage**

| Collection Method | Applicable Services/Applications | Data Types Collected | Configuration |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **Container Insights** | • dbt containers • Airbyte containers | • Container stdout/stderr logs • System metrics (CPU, memory, disk I/O, network) • Container restart events • Application logs | • Built-in ACI integration • Automatic log forwarding • Direct to customer hub LAW • No additional configuration |
| **Native Azure Monitor Integration** | • Fabric Managed Airflow (ADF) • Azure DevOps Agents | • DAG execution metrics • Task success/failure rates • Pipeline run duration • Scheduler performance • CI/CD execution logs | • Built-in integration • Automatic forwarding • No additional config needed • Direct to customer LAW |
| **Azure Diagnostic Settings** | • Azure Database for PostgreSQL • ADLS Gen2 (Landing Zone) • Key Vault • Container Registry • Container Instances • Network Security Groups | • Resource metrics • Operation logs • Performance counters • Access patterns • Request/response metrics • Resource health events | • Configured via Terraform • Policy-enforced settings • Points to customer hub LAW • Managed identity auth |
| **Fabric Workspace Monitoring** | • Fabric Workspaces • OneLake (all medallion layers) • Fabric notebooks • Spark jobs • Data pipelines | • Capacity unit consumption • Storage utilization • Job execution metrics • Data movement volumes • Query performance | • Fabric Admin APIs • Workspace activity logs • Capacity metrics API • REST API monitoring |
| **Azure Cost Management** | • All Azure Resources • Resource Groups • Subscriptions | • Daily cost accumulation • Budget threshold breaches • Cost by service/tag • Forecast vs actual | • Native integration • Budget alerts via Action Groups • Exports to LAW • Daily scheduled exports |

**Note:** Log retention is controlled by the customer's hub LAW configuration. Elementary reports are stored with timestamp paths to maintain history in observability storage with platform-managed retention (30 days default, configurable in governance.tfvars).

### **1.2 Data Platform Observability**

| Component | Log Types | Collection Path | Query Example |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **Airbyte** | • Connection test results • Sync start/completion • Records read/written • Error stacktraces | Container Insights → LAW | `ContainerLog | where ContainerName contains "airbyte"` |
| **dbt** | • Model compilation • SQL execution • Test results • Lineage metadata | Container Insights → LAW | `ContainerLog | where ContainerName contains "dbt"` |
| **Airflow** | • DAG parsing • Task execution • Queue status • Worker health | Native Azure Monitor → LAW | `AzureDiagnostics | where ResourceType == "DATAFACTORIES"` |
| **Elementary** | • Freshness checks • Volume anomalies • Schema drift • Custom tests | Container Insights → LAW | `ContainerLog | where Message contains "elementary"` |

**Note:** Log retention is controlled by the customer's hub LAW configuration, not by the platform. End-to-end Pipeline Tracking is not in the current design. 

## **2\. Service-Specific Telemetry Matrix**

| Service/Application | Primary Collection Method | Secondary Method | Key Metrics Collected |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **dbt Core** | Container Insights | \- | • Execution logs  • Error messages  • Completion status  • Container metrics  |
| **Airbyte Platform** | Container Insights | PostgreSQL Diagnostics | • Sync logs  • Error messages  • Container metrics  • DB performance (via PostgreSQL)  |
| **Fabric Managed Airflow** | Native Azure Monitor | \- | • DAG run status • Task execution time • Queue depth • Worker utilization |
| **OneLake** | Fabric Workspace Monitoring | \- | • Data ingestion rate (Bronze) • Transformation metrics (Silver) • Query patterns (Gold) • Storage growth across layers |
| **PostgreSQL (Airbyte)** | Diagnostic Settings | \- | • Query performance • Connection pool • Storage usage • Transaction rates |
| **ADLS Gen2 (Landing)** | Diagnostic Settings | \- | • Write throughput • Read operations • Storage capacity • Access latency |
| **Container Instances** | Diagnostic Settings |  | • CPU utilization • Memory consumption • Container restarts • Network I/O |
| **Key Vault** | Diagnostic Settings | \- | • Secret retrieval • Authentication success • Operation latency • Request volume |
| **CI/CD Runners** | Native Azure Monitor | \- | • Pipeline execution time • Job success rate • Queue wait time • Agent availability |
| **Network Components** | Diagnostic Settings (NSG only) | \- | • NSG rule hits • Blocked/allowed traffic • Connection attempts • Basic flow data |

## **3\. Cost Monitoring and Alerting**

Cost monitoring integrates with Azure Monitor for centralized logging and analysis:

| Budget Type | Scope | Action |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **Subscription Budget** | Entire dev/prod subscription | Log to LAW only |
| **Resource Group Budgets** | Each resource group | Log to LAW only |
| **Service-Specific Budgets** | High-cost services (Fabric, ACI) via filters | Log to LAW only |

**Cost Data Collection:**

- Budget thresholds configured in `config/02_governance.tfvars`  
- All budget events logged to Log Analytics Workspace for analysis  
- Cost data exported daily to LAW for dashboard creation  
- No email notifications or action groups configured in current phase

**Configuration via config/02\_governance.tfvars:**

```
# Subscription Budget
subscription_budget = {
  monthly_limit = 10000
  alert_threshold = 80
  notification_emails = []  # Empty for logging only
}

# Resource-Specific Budgets (subscription scope with filters)
resource_budgets = {
  storage = {
    monthly_limit = 1000
    alert_threshold = 80
    filter_resource_types = ["Microsoft.Storage"]
    notification_emails = []  # Empty for logging only
  }
  data_platform = {
    monthly_limit = 5000
    alert_threshold = 80
    filter_resource_types = ["Microsoft.Fabric", "Microsoft.ContainerInstance"]
    filter_services = ["Azure Data Factory", "Container Instances"]
    notification_emails = []  # Empty for logging only
  }
  networking = {
    monthly_limit = 500
    alert_threshold = 75
    filter_resource_types = ["Microsoft.Network"]
    notification_emails = []  # Empty for logging only
  }
}
```
